# Code Quality Standards (plan-an-go)

This repo is Bash/shell only. No TypeScript, Next.js, or frontend stack.

## Bash script best practices (scripts in scripts/)

- Use `#!/bin/bash` with `set -e` and `set -o pipefail`. Keep scripts portable for macOS/Linux.
- Quote all expansions: `"$var"`, `"${arr[@]}"`. For lists of paths, use arrays and `"${arr[@]}"` in loops.
- Initialize loop/state variables before use (e.g. `PREV_ARG=""` before arg-parsing loops) so scripts are safe under `set -u` if adopted.
- Prefer a `cleanup()` function and `trap cleanup EXIT` for temp files; only `rm -f` when the variable is set (e.g. `[ -n "${temp_file:-}" ] && rm -f "$temp_file"`).
- Send user-facing errors to stderr: `echo "ERROR: ..." >&2` and `exit 1`.
- Use `mktemp` for temp files; avoid fixed names in `/tmp`.

## Naming and layout

- Script names: `plan-an-go-*.sh` in `scripts/cli/` and `scripts/system/`.
- Environment variables: uppercase, prefixed with `PLAN_AN_GO_` (see `docs/ENV-README.md`).
- Two-space indentation; descriptive variable names.

## Comments

- Only meaningful comments: logical steps, non-obvious "why" reasoning.
- No trivial comments that restate the code. No emoji in code or comments.

## Quality gates

- Run `npm run lint` (ShellCheck) and `npm run check` (lint + format) before commits.
- Use `npm run format:write` to fix shell formatting (shfmt). Requires shellcheck and shfmt (e.g. `brew install shellcheck shfmt`).
